<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Mahjong is a game for four players that originated in China. It was called, meaning sparrow in ancient China, which is still the name most commonly used in some southern Chinese dialects such as Cantonese and Minnan, as well as in Japanese. However, most Mandarin-speaking Chinese now call the game má jiàng.
     			<br><br>Ron-Ron (Dragon Dragon) is a puzzle game originally released in 1994, appeared first in the arcades and released for Playstation and Saturn consoles in different game versions.
     			<br><br>RULES:
     			<br>The same pattern tiles stacked on the screen (Flower tiles, tile season is considered the same pattern but with different flowers and their seasons. And so on) to select two tiles in pairs, will be removed. You can select when connected by straight vertical or horizontal through the tiles of two similar, if less than twice the number of bend lines (ie, between the tiles of two with a combination of vertical lines or horizontal lines within three When a tie) is.
     			<br><br>GAMEPLAY:
     			<br>As in the Shanghai games series matching 2 tiles of the same kind make them dissappear and to win the player have to clear the table.
     			<br><br>The Ron Ron (Value 1500) (aka The Ryuu Ryuu) is a conversion of the Ron-Ron game made by Sunsoft that features lots of challenging puzzles and the options of go back to the previous movement.
     			<br><br>More information about Ron-Ron (in japanese) here:
     			<br>http://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E9%BE%8D%E9%BE%8D
     			<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Absolutely "timeout", "stalemate" can not be cleared for the players, "get back" one "tile view" hidden feature or help, such as free play time can be set, from beginner to advanced, thoroughly enjoyable The.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>First person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Ron-Ron & Mahjong themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

